    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Evaluating conditions using Python¥n",
        "Apart from arithmetic operations, Python also provides several oprations for comparing numbers & variables.¥n",
        "¥n",
        "Operator¥tDescription¥n",
        "==¥tCheck if operands are equal¥n",
        "!=¥tCheck if operands are not equal¥n",
        ">¥tCheck if left operand is greater than right operand¥n",
        "<¥tCheck if left operand is less than right operand¥n",
        ">=¥tCheck if left operand is greater than or equal to right operand¥n",
        "<=¥tCheck if left operand is less than or equal to right operand¥n",
        "The result of a comparision operation is either True or False (note the uppercase T and F). These are special keywords in Python. Let's try out some experiment with comparision operators."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Yi3_3gnlFiaQ"
      }
