      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Combining conditions with logical operators¥n",
        "¥n",
        "The logical operators `and`, `or` and `not` operate upon conditions and `True` & `False` values (also known as *booleans*). `and` and `or` operate on two conditions, whereas `not` operates on a single condition.¥n",
        "¥n",
        "The `and` operator returns `True` when both the conditions evalute to `True`. Otherwise it returns `False`.¥n",
        "¥n",
        "| `a`     | `b`    | `a and b` |¥n",
        "|---------|--------|-----------|¥n",
        "|  `True` | `True` | `True`    |¥n",
        "|  `True` | `False`| `False`   |¥n",
        "|  `False`| `True` | `False`   |¥n",
        "|  `False`| `False`| `False`   |¥n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "beGiUpw7HmL_"
      }
    },
